Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, the presidential candidate of the New Nigerian Peoples Party (NNPP), says his party has the political ability to end insecurity across the country and rebuild the economy. Kwankwaso who spoke at the party’s Northeast presidential zonal rally on Thursday in Bauchi, urged fellow Nigerians to vote for the party in the forthcoming general election. The former Kano State governor criticised the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) for not doing enough to tackle the nation’s woes in the last two decades they led the country. READ ALSO: 2023 Election: INEC Extends Deadline For PVC Collection “Let me use this opportunity to tell the people of the Northeast and Nigeria as a whole that our party, the NNPP, has come of age now. We are in all the wards of this country. “They have failed the country in terms of security, in terms of economy, in terms of infrastructure; even in terms of unity among Nigerians,” he said.